Reasoning: The paper deals with the broadcast throughput in wireless networks, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of network coding and routing algorithms also suggests that the paper could be categorized under distributed computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the study of radio networks as a mathematical model could also place the paper under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
